# Horizon — Install & Run Guide

## What you need first

Install these on your laptop before anything else:

1. **Node.js** — https://nodejs.org → download the "LTS" version and run the installer
2. **VS Code** — https://code.visualstudio.com → download and install
3. **Git** (optional but recommended) — https://git-scm.com

To check Node.js installed correctly, open a terminal and type:
```
node -v
npm -v
```
Both should print a version number (e.g. v20.x.x).

---

## Step 1 — Copy the project folder

Take the `horizon` folder you downloaded and place it anywhere on your laptop.
For example: `C:\Users\YourName\Projects\horizon` (Windows) or `~/Projects/horizon` (Mac/Linux).

---

## Step 2 — Open in VS Code

1. Open VS Code
2. Go to **File → Open Folder**
3. Select the `horizon` folder
4. VS Code will open the project

---

## Step 3 — Open the terminal in VS Code

In VS Code, press:
- **Windows/Linux**: `` Ctrl + ` `` (backtick key)
- **Mac**: `` Cmd + ` ``

A terminal panel opens at the bottom.

---

## Step 4 — Install dependencies

In the terminal, type this and press Enter:

```bash
npm install
```

This downloads all the React libraries the project needs.
It will take 1–2 minutes. You'll see a `node_modules` folder appear.

---

## Step 5 — Run the app

In the terminal, type:

```bash
npm start
```

Your browser will automatically open at:
```
http://localhost:3000
```

Horizon is now running! Any changes you make to the code will instantly update in the browser.

---

## Project structure explained

```
horizon/
├── public/
│   └── index.html          ← The HTML shell (don't change this much)
├── src/
│   ├── index.js            ← Entry point (don't change)
│   ├── index.css           ← Global styles and color variables
│   ├── App.js              ← Main app — controls which tab/view is shown
│   ├── data/
│   │   └── templates.js    ← ALL job types, sections, and fields live here
│   └── components/
│       ├── Sidebar.jsx         ← Left nav, role switcher, job list
│       ├── Topbar.jsx          ← Top bar with title and action buttons
│       ├── RequestsDashboard.jsx ← "My Requests" tab with stats + table
│       ├── TemplateBuilder.jsx ← HR's template editor
│       ├── ManagerPreview.jsx  ← What the hiring manager sees
│       └── RolePermissions.jsx ← Toggle permissions per role
└── package.json            ← Project config and dependencies
```

