## How to customize

### Add a new job type (e.g. "Legal")
Open `src/data/templates.js` and add a new entry to `JOB_TEMPLATES`:

```js
Legal: {
  color: 'teal',
  sections: [
    {
      id: 'leg-summary',
      name: 'Job summary',
      tag: 'Core',
      locked: false,
      fields: [
        { id: 'title', label: 'Job title', type: 'text', required: true, placeholder: 'e.g. Corporate Counsel' },
        { id: 'practice', label: 'Practice area', type: 'select', options: ['Corporate', 'IP', 'Employment', 'Compliance'] },
      ],
    },
    // add more sections...
  ],
},
```

### Add a section to an existing job
Find the job in `JOB_TEMPLATES` and add an object to its `sections` array.

### Change colors
Open `src/index.css` and edit the `:root` variables.
For example, change `--blue: #185FA5;` to any hex color you want.

### Add a new field type
Fields support these `type` values:
- `text` — single line text input
- `textarea` — multi-line text
- `select` — dropdown (add an `options: []` array)
- `checkboxes` — multiple checkboxes (add an `options: []` array)
- `number` — numeric input
- `date` — date picker

